<h2>You can follow CES via social media while you are at the show and all year long. </h2>
<p class="intro">Get industry news, win cool prizes and learn more about the world&rsquo;s most important technology event as news for it breaks. Want to join the conversation? Be sure to use our official hashtag #CES2015.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
The 2014 CES was a huge success both on the show floor and on social media. Our official hashtag (#CES2014) was mentioned over 400,000 times and had a reach of 40 percent of the world&rsquo;s population.&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
We partnered with FleishmanHillard&rsquo;s black box, an interactive, portable, human-powered technology platform that integrates business data into real-time insight dashboards and visualizations to help funnel all the chatter happening about the show. They allowed attendees to see what was trending, where in the world people were talking about CES and more. The biggest trend of the show on social media was wearable tech, making up half of the conversations on the first day.&nbsp;<br />
